The Chronicle Thupeyo Muleya TEN people among them four minors escaped death by a whisker when a house they were sleeping in caught fire in Tshithaudze Suburb in Beitbridge on Wednesday morning. According to Beitbridge Municipality’s Head of Emergency Services Mr George Maseko the fire broke out at around 5AM. He said the house and a vehicle which was parked in the yard were reduced to shells. More to follow…